cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper deals with a problem in computer vision (object detection) and proposes a novel approach using deep neural networks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves learning and optimization techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with predicting sets, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also mentions a complex CAPTCHA test, which involves natural language processing and could be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
